Kenya Kwanza presidential candidate William Ruto will on Monday take his campaigns to Nairobi county. His itinerary will start at Retail before heading to Gikomba, in Starehe constituency. In the afternoon, the trail will head to Pumwani still in Kamukunji, before proceeding to Jogoo Road/Uhuru Market and finish at Bahati in Makadara constituency. The DP will be accompanied by leaders allied to the coalition to drum up support for their bid. On Saturday and Sunday, Ruto campaigned in Kiambu county. Azimio Presidential candidate Raila Odinga will on the other hand hold an open day. Raila together with his running mate Martha Karua on Saturday and Sunday campaigned in Nairobi. This is part of efforts by the Azimio and Kenya Kwanza coalitions to ensure that they have control of the city after the August 9 polls. The 2022 general election has been labelled the most competitive with much at stake for the two leading presidential contenders.